
  Hi Safiyeh!

  Well, I must thank you for making me fix these long-standing problems
  in the seqdiff program, otherwise I never would have!
  
  I've added seperate "gap start" and "gap continue" penalties to the
  alignment scoring system.  Now it penalizes 5 points to start a gap,
  but only 1 point to continue a gap once it has been started. (substitutions
  cost 4 points).  This seems (?) to have fixed the alignment problems at the
  ends, which you showed me.
  
  However, I noticed a few cases in your data which now have large (30-40bp)
  gaps WITHIN the alignments.  Take a look at the example below- does this
  look right to you?

=sean


